\textbf{(a)} 0\% compression, \textbf{(b)} 4\% compression, \textbf{(c)} 8\% compression, \textbf{(d)} 10\% compression, \textbf{(e)} 12\% compression, \textbf{(f)} 15\% compression.
WS\textsubscript{2} undergoes a direct-to-indirect band gap crossover at moderate compressions, similar to MoS\textsubscript{2}, with pronounced valence band flattening beyond 10\%.}
\label{fig:S5}
\end{figure}

\begin{figure}[h!]
