\textbf{(a)} 0\% compression, \textbf{(b)} 4\% compression, \textbf{(c)} 8\% compression, \textbf{(d)} 10\% compression, \textbf{(e)} 12\% compression, \textbf{(f)} 15\% compression.
While WSe\textsubscript{2} requires higher compressions to trigger the transition, significant flattening of the valence band near $\Gamma$ is ultimately observed.}
\label{fig:S6}
