Top row: CBM states; Bottom row: VBM states.
\textbf{(a)} 0\%, \textbf{(b)} 4\%, \textbf{(c)} 8\%, \textbf{(d)} 10\%, \textbf{(e)} 12\%, \textbf{(f)} 15\% compression.
Despite requiring greater compression, WSe\textsubscript{2} ultimately exhibits strong hole localization driven by ripple curvature.}
